OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This creek consists almost entirely of pools and runs.  The sampling site is located off the bridge on Furnace Road in southern Chancellorsville Battlefield Park and is downstream of the second junction of creeks that originate outside of the park boundaries.  This site is also downstream of the sampling site on Lewis Run (CR05).  The creek runs southeast through a forested area of the park before exiting the property.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The sampling area on Wilderness Run is located near the picnic area off HillEwell Drive in Wilderness Battlefield Park.  The creek originates outside of the park boundaries in a forested area and once inside the park, winds northeast past agricultural lands before it joins with South Wilderness Run and exits the park at Plank Road.  This sampling area contains a mixture of pools, runs and riffles.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This section of Wilderness Run will be accessed by the bridge off HillEwell Drive in Wilderness Battlefield Park.  The creek originates outside of the park in a cleared section of woodlands and flows northeast through the park.  The watershed upstream of the sampling site contains primarily woodlands and agricultural areas.  Downstream from the site, the creek flows into Wilderness Run lake and then joins North Wilderness Run before exiting the park at Plank Road.  This creek contains mostly pools and runs.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The sampling site at Elwood is located downstream of the junction of North Wilderness Run and South Wilderness Run.  The site is accessible from the field beside the main road into Elwood.  The watershed upstream of the site is a combination of residential, agricultural and woodland areas.  After Elwood, Wilderness Run flows northeast out of the park at Plank Road.  This section of Wilderness Run contains mainly pools and runs.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This creek flows through the area of Wilderness Battlefield that is north of Constitution Highway.  This site was a part of the original water monitoring plan of the park back in the 1990s.  The creek can also be accessed from its intersection with Constitution Hwy near Plank Road.  The watershed upstream of the sampling site contains residential and commercial areas.  The creek contains primarily runs and pools.
